        <updateDate>2022-02-28T14:22:06Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Smarter Approaches to Nuclear Expenditures Act</strong></p> <p>This bill imposes prohibitions and limitations on funding for various Department of Defense (DOD) and Department of Energy (DOE) weapons programs.</p> <p>Weapons subjected to prohibitions or limitations under this bill include Columbia-class submarines, intercontinental ballistic missiles, low-yield nuclear warheads, and space-based missile defense systems.</p> <p>The bill also requires various reports to Congress, including a joint report from DOD and DOE outlining the estimated cost savings resulting from this bill.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
